    <item>
      <title>about</title>
      <link>http://msteenhagen.github.io/home/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Apr 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://msteenhagen.github.io/home/about/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;h1 id=&#34;what-are-the-limits-of-perception&#34;&gt;What are the limits of perception?&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am a Lecturer in philosophy at the University of Cambridge, and a Visiting Research Fellow at the Institute of Advanced Studies of University College London.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My research focuses on perception and the mind. In particular, I concentrate on the role of perceptual media&amp;mdash;such as sounds, images, and optical technology. So far my articles have covered the experience of sounds, images, and mirror perception. I also like to dabble into controversies about philosophical method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I teach Philosophical Logic, Theory of Meaning, Metaphysics of Persons, and a number of lecture series in the Philosophy of Mind and Cognitive Science.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Besides writing about and teaching philosophy I am a coffee nerd and web developer.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
